## Downward Flow (Cleanup)

When a cluster gets promoted from layer N to layer N-1 (higher = more universal), all lower-layer copies must be removed. Otherwise the same rule exists in three places, drifting independently.

Trigger: PR against the destination layer's repo merges, GitHub Action fires.

```
PR merged at layer N ─> GitHub Action ─> identify cluster ID
                                              │
                                              ▼
                                        query cluster:<id>:repos
                                        and *:rules indices for
                                        all lower-layer locations
                                              │
                                              ▼
                                        enqueue (cluster_id, location)
                                        pairs into queue:cleanup
                                              │
                                              ▼
                                  ┌───────────┴───────────┐
                                  ▼                       ▼
                          cleanup worker            superseded marker
                          (repo PRs)                (auto-memory targets)
                                  │                       │
                                  ▼                       ▼
                          generates removal PR      next /promote-learnings
                          via GitHub App            run on each engineer's
                          against each repo,        machine sees superseded
                          description references    flag, proposes local
                          superseding rule          edits; Auto Dream cleans
                                                    up on next pass
```

Auto-memory cleanup is per-engineer and not centrally writable — handled via a "superseded" marker on the cluster that engineers' next harvester run picks up.

