## Conflict Cases

The system must handle without humans:

| Case | Handling |
|---|---|
| Concurrent promotion | Lock on `cluster:<id>:promoting`; second promotion no-ops |
| Rule edited at higher layer mid-cleanup | Cleanup worker re-fetches canonical text before merging cleanup PR; removal still correct regardless |
| Repo rule that legitimately overrides org rule | Detect by structural comparison: superset of constraints, or explicit reference to general rule. Flag for human review, don't auto-cleanup |
| Cleanup PR rejected by repo owner | Mark cluster `cleanup_exempted` for that repo, don't re-propose, surface in triage UI |
| Stale clusters | Age-based GC: no new occurrences in 6 months + no current-layer presence → archive |
| Embedding drift (rephrased same learning becomes different cluster) | Periodic offline pass that re-clusters using stricter similarity; merges discovered duplicates |

