## Stack Decisions

| Component | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Cluster store | Redis Enterprise with AOF | Already operational; RediSearch HNSW for vectors in same cluster; better persistence than MemoryDB; Active-Active CRDTs available |
| Vector index | RediSearch HNSW | Same cluster as cluster store, single query path, no external vector DB |
| Ingestion API | API Gateway + Lambda, SigV4 via Okta → IAM Identity Center | Inherits org SSO; access logs provide audit of who promoted what without storing identity in cluster data |
| Audit log | SQS → Lambda → S3 with daily-rotated append-only objects | Standard append-only pattern; Athena-queryable later; decouples ingestion from audit retention |
| Classifier + embeddings | Claude API from ingestion Lambda | No infra to run; uses same model family as Claude Code itself |
| Promotion worker | Scheduled Lambda | Drains fast-track queue; drafts PRs via GitHub App |
| GitHub identity | Existing GitHub App (no personal credentials, no generated-by trailers) | Inherits supply-chain hardening posture; clean PR attribution |
| Triage UI | React + TypeScript, S3 + CloudFront, API Gateway behind SigV4 SSO | Internal tool for DevEx; bundler chosen at build time |
| Lambdas | TypeScript on Node 20 | Same language as UI and CDK; first-class AWS SDK v3 and Anthropic SDK support; fast cold start; I/O-bound workload doesn't need a faster runtime |
| Infrastructure | CDK in TypeScript | Same language as runtime; no separate infra DSL |
| Local sources | `/promote-learnings` slash command + GitHub Actions on merged PRs; TypeScript scripts invoked from Markdown commands | Distributed via existing `~/.claude` dotfiles repo (commands and hooks already in share list) |

**TypeScript everywhere.** Frontend, Lambdas, CDK, local scripts. One language, one toolchain, one set of types shared between API request/response shapes and the UI consuming them.

**No server framework.** Lambdas are individual handlers parsing events, calling Claude, hitting Redis, returning. There is no long-running process to host, no request multiplexing, no ASGI/middleware to configure. The framework is the Lambda runtime.

**Explicitly rejected:**
- MemoryDB (good for prototyping, insufficient for production)
- Redis Streams as audit log (use SQS → S3)
- Storing engineer identity in cluster data (not needed; velocity from weighted occurrences; audit from API Gateway logs)
- DynamoDB (Redis Enterprise is the operational muscle)
- Quasar for the triage UI (overkill for internal tool)
- FastAPI / any server framework (no long-running process exists in this architecture; was a ExampleProject-ism that doesn't belong in greenfield)
- Python or Rust for Lambdas (TypeScript wins for language unification with frontend and CDK; workload is I/O-bound so Rust's CPU performance is wasted)

