## Sequencing / Rollout

| Phase | Scope | Dependencies |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Local-only `/promote-learnings` for one engineer (Edwin). No backend. Classify-and-draft-PR locally. | Validates taxonomy + routing logic. |
| 2 | Ingestion endpoint + Redis cluster store + cross-source dedup, no opt-out. Upward promotion only. | Phase 1 taxonomy. |
| 3 | GitHub Actions for repo `CLAUDE.md` / `rules` extraction (Source 2). Agent-authored repo learnings feed pipeline. | Phase 2 backend. |
| 4 | Cleanup workers, auto-memory direction first (lowest blast radius — superseded markers are advisory until engineers harvest). | Phase 3. |
| 5 | Cleanup workers for repo cleanup PRs. Higher blast radius — needs solid conflict handling. | Phase 4. |
| 6 | Enterprise policy as a source. Full org-user → repo cleanup path. | Phase 5. |

Each phase is independently useful. Phases 1-3 deliver the upward flow before any downward complexity ships.

