## Deferred to v2 / Open Questions

- **Cleanup of redundant repo rules** when org-level rule lands. Needs solid conflict handling to avoid blasting unwanted PRs across 100+ repos. Phase 5.
- **Embedding similarity threshold tuning.** Won't know the right values until real auto-memory data flows. The piece that determines whether clusters end up coherent or drift.
- **Stack-shared layer mechanics.** Settled by the loading semantics: stack rules go in `~/.claude/rules/<stack>.md` with `paths:` frontmatter so they lazy-load only when Claude touches matching files. A separately-imported shared knowledge repo is unnecessary unless the org wants per-team rule subsets that not all engineers should receive — at which point the dotfiles repo's whitelist mechanism could fork into per-team variants. Defer that until evidence demands it.
- **Cross-repo abstraction (the original "100+ repos" question).** Once the harvester is operating, Claude can do the abstraction itself by looking at deduplicated learnings across the corpus. Not a separate system to design.
- **Feedback to Anthropic on Claude Code defaults.** The git-pull-after-merge example is a learning Claude shouldn't need; suggests defaults could be tighter. Out of band from this system.

